<FIRST>r a AM-Biaggi-Prison 1stLd-Writethru a0746 04-09 0258</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Biaggi-Prison, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0746,0261</SECOND>
<HEAD>Precede NEWARK, N.J.</HEAD>
<HEAD>Biaggi Maintains Innocence As He Flies To Prison</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 4 grafs to UPDATE with Biaggi's arrival in Texas.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRAPEVINE, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former New York Rep. Mario Biaggi
arrived in Texas on Sunday to begin his 2{-year prison term for a
bribery conviction.
   Before leaving for Dallas-Fort Worth International Airport,
Biaggi told reporters at Newark International Airport in New Jersey
that he went to church earlier Sunday and visited his wife, Marie
Wassil Biaggi, who is hospitalized with Hodgkin's disease.
   Flanked by family members, the 71-year-old Biaggi smiled often
as he used a cane to walk aboard the Continental Airlines flight
taking him to Fort Worth.
   The former congressman is expected to turn himself in to U.S.
Correctional Facility officials there on Monday and begin serving
his 2{-year sentence.
   ``I have loving grandchildren and loving children,'' Biaggi
said. ``They'll be here when I get back.''
   The 10-term congressman in the Bronx-Westchester district was
convicted on federal bribery charges in September 1987 for
accepting a Florida spa vacation from former Brooklyn Democratic
boss Meade Esposito in exchange for Biaggi's efforts on behalf of a
ship repair company.
   Biaggi was later convicted in Manhattan Federal Court in
connection with the Wedtech scandal and sentenced to eight years.
That conviction is under appeal.
   Biaggi has maintained he accepted the Florida vacation as a
friend of Esposito.
   ``I find myself going to a federal facility today because a
friend of some 35 years was generous to me,'' he said.
</TEXT>
