<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--SouthKorea-Student     04-09 0122</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--South Korea-Student,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Student who set self afire dies from burns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A college student who set himself
afire in his classroom in an anti-American protest died Saturday at
a hospital, officials reported.
   Nam Tae-hyun, 24, a senior at Seoul Normal College, doused
gasoline over his body and set it ablaze Friday night.
   Friends said they heard Nam shouting ``Yankee go home and
national unification!'' as they rushed into the room.
   Self-immolation is frequently used by South Korean dissidents to
dramatize their anger. About a dozen people have committed suicide
by setting themseves afire since 1980.
   Anti-government students say the 42,000 U.S. military personnel
stationed in South Korea block unification of the country with
communist North Korea.
</TEXT>
