<SECOND>AM-BRF--Italy-Demonstration,0116</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thousands Demonstrate Against NATO and U.S. Fighter Planes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thousands of demonstrators marched through downtown
Saturday to protest a new base for U.S. F-16 fighter bombers in
southern Italy.
   The protesters also demanded that all NATO bases in Europe be
closed.
   At least 10,000 people took part in the march, organizers said.
Police put the number at closer to 4,000.
   Protesters carried a large banner that said ``No to NATO _ No to
the F-16s.''
   The sign referred to the government's decision last year to host
a squadron of the fighter bombers, which are being moved from their
base in Spain to Calabria, Italy's far southern province.
