<FILEID>AP-NR-04-09-89 1124EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u a BC-MotelExplosion 1stLd-Writethru a0623 04-09 0311</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Motel Explosion, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0623,0314</SECOND>
<HEAD>Explosion Rocks Motel; One Missing</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughout with explosion apparently caused by natural
gas leak; one person missing; other detail. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BILLINGS, Mont. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion apparently caused by a
natural gas leak demolished a 40-foot section of a motel early
Sunday morning, injuring 31 people, authorities said. One man was
missing.
   ``The center of the building is gone, and then there's fire
damage both ways,'' said Charlie Allen, acting battalion chief for
the Billings Fire Department.
   The explosion occurred shortly after 1 a.m. at the three-story
Super 8 Lodge in this south-central Montana city of 75,000.
Authorities said about 60 people were staying in the motel and it
was about half full.
   Dick Blee, the acting Billings fire chief, said Montana-Dakota
Utilities received a telephone call, presumably from an employee of
the motel, who said there was a strong smell of natural gas. The
explosion followed about four minutes later, he said.
   One man, described as a truck driver who was staying at the
motel, was missing. Spokeswomen for the city's two major hospitals
said 31 people had been treated for injuries and two were admitted.
   Heavy machinery was being moved to the site near Interstate 90
to remove the larger pieces of debris, Allen said.
   Firefighters had the blaze under control by 4 a.m., Allen said,
and the area around the motel remained blocked off to the public.
   Blee said a truck belonging to the missing man was in the motel
parking lot. Earlier, authorities had feared that more people were
missing; Blee said there were problems accounting for some motel
occupants because they left after the explosion.
   The explosion appeared to be in a laundry in the center of the
motel, Blee said, an area with natural-gas lines. Individual rooms
in the motel have electric heat.
</TEXT>
