<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--11thCommandment     04-09 0102</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--11th Commandment,0103</SECOND>
<HEAD>Verily, Verily, Thou Shalt Not Park Here</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CRAWLEY, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Roman Catholic priest has come up with
his own 11th Commandment: ``Thou shalt not even think of parking
here.''
   The gospel according to the Rev. Matthew McInerney is proclaimed
on a notice outside his church in Crawley, 27 miles south of London.
   The sign is part of his battle with motorists who park in front
of the church and block hearses.
   ``People who don't have permits should not park here, but they
still do it,'' McInerney said Sunday. ``Like the other 10
commandments, it is ignored.''
</TEXT>
