named, JANA said, ``We reaffirm, once again, that these claims are
lies and groundless and we renew our bewilderment at this strange
determination by the mass media in continuing the promotion of
these lies.''
   U.S. F-111 aircraft operating from Britain bombed Libya on April
15, 1986, in retaliation for terrorist attacks allegedly plotted by
Libya that killed five Americans.
